%h2
  Sections

#sections_box.splitcontentleft{ :style => 'width: 66%;' }
  %p
    This is the sections page, here is the list of sections within your website, to watch the pages within each section, you only need to click a section name, and you will be redirected to that particular section page where you will be able to add pages, edit the section name, and adding subsections.
  %br

  %table.list
    %thead
      %tr
        %th
          Name
        %th
          Created at
        %th
          Last updated at
        %th
          Operations

    - oddity = 1
    - @sections.each do |section|
      %tr{ :class => ( oddity %2 == 0 )? '' : 'odd' }
        - oddity =  oddity + 1

        %td
          = link_to section.name, section_path(section)
        %td
          = section.created_at.strftime("%B, %d %Y")
        %td
          = section.updated_at.strftime("%B, %d %Y")
        %td
          = link_to 'Edit', edit_section_path(section)
          = link_to 'Destroy', section, :confirm => 'Are you sure?', :method => :delete

  = will_paginate @sections

#tips_content.splitcontentright.box{ :style => 'width: 29%;' }
  %h3
    Did you know?
  %p
    CloverInteractive's Clever CMS automatically creates friendly urls based on your section, subsection and page names.
  %p
    Apart from being user friendly, friendly urls allow you to improve your position in the most popular search engines result pages, and let you keep your pages clean and organized.

